{"TopicId":132133,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Open/close multiple fuel tanks simultaneously","CreatedByName":"fireblade274","CreatedById":134571,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-15T02:51:28Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"fireblade274","CreatedById":134571,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-15T02:51:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a mod that simply lets you open or close multiple fuel tanks simultaneously, very much like an action group?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NoMrBond","CreatedById":69263,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-15T03:36:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/23808-102-tac-fuel-balancer-v251-2may/\u0022\u003ETAC Fuel Balancer\u003C/a\u003E and Goodspeed Fuel Pump (now \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/106448-gpospeedfuelpump-ksp-v102/\u0022\u003EGPO\u003C/a\u003E) let you do tank/storage related manipulations, hopefully one of them will do what you looking for\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fireblade274","CreatedById":134571,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-15T03:41:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTAC only works on 1.02 atm, and i dont think GPO does what i want it to do, unless someone knows something i dont\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"birdog357","CreatedById":150790,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-16T00:51:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTac works fine in 1.0.5.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nathan1","CreatedById":144486,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-16T15:51:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/116142-105jul1615-modactions-control-your-vessel-including-other-mods-via-actiongroups/\u0022\u003EMod Actions\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0will do what you want through action groups.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"genericeventhandler","CreatedById":149557,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-17T09:38:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmart parts has bits you put between tanks that can be action grouped to allow / restrict flow. I put them around the ISRU and it\u0027s tanks so I don\u0027t get thrust issues if it is running.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}